; ── SYNTHETIC PLACEHOLDER SEQUENCES ──────────────────────────────────────
;
; These sequences are NOT real McrA protein sequences.
; They are synthetic amino acid strings used only to demonstrate the API.
;
; To obtain verified M. acetivorans C2A McrA protein sequence:
;   UniProt: Q8TN35  (McrA, M. acetivorans C2A)
;   NCBI:    NP_618892.1
;   https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/protein/NP_618892.1
;
; To obtain M. marburgensis McrA (PDB reference sequence):
;   UniProt: P11558
;   PDB:     1MRO chain A
;   https://www.rcsb.org/structure/1MRO
;
; Quick download of M. acetivorans McrA protein:
;   efetch -db protein -id NP_618892.1 -format fasta > McrA_acetivorans.faa
; ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

; Synthetic sequence of length 553 (matches M. marburgensis reference length)
; with correct residue types (G, H, R, Q, C) placed at known PTM positions:
;   G445 (thioglycine), H257 (1-N-methylhistidine), R271 (5-methylarginine),
;   Q400 (2-methylglutamine), C452 (S-methylcysteine)
